-- IDBI Bank Agrees $125 Million Three-Year Term Loan With Banks, E-Mail Says
-- B y   S h e l l e y   S m i t h
-- 2010-11-01T02:24:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/idbi-bank-agrees-125-million-three-year-term-loan-with-banks-e-mail-says.html
IDBI Bank Ltd. agreed to borrow $125
million, according an e-mailed statement today.  BNP Paribas, Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc, Standard
Chartered Plc, Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ and United Overseas
Bank Ltd. arranged the three-year term loan, according to the
statement from the Mumbai-based company.  The funds raised will be used for general corporate
purposes, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
